         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">8/8/92 ¶  ¶ You will see from the enclosed sheet, ¶  highly esteemed Doctor, that Dr Ramsay, Director of the zoological museum of Sydney, also will subscribe to the continuation of your important Char...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">92.08.08a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Otto Nordstedt</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Handskr. avdl., Universitetsbibliotek, Lund.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">8/8/92</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sie werden aus dem beigefügten Blatte ersehen, hochgeehrter Herr Doctor, dass Dr Ramsay, der Director des zool. Museums von Sydney, auch auf die Fortsetzung Ihrer wichtigen Characeen-Monographie subscribiren will. Mr Maiden in Sydney hat ein zweites Exemplar bestellt. Wenn wir erst wissen, ob die Fortsetzung auf Subscription möglich ist, werden sich auch noch Andere finden lassen für Abnehmen des Werkes.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Sie ehrend der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">Nun ist denn auch der vort[r]effliche Schübeler dahin! So scheidet Einer nach dem Anderen meiner vieljährigen Freunde aus dem Leben, u werde ich wohl Regel, Todaro u so vielen Anderen bald folgen!</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sie werden demnächst wieder einige Characeen erhalten, da Herr Eckert die Arten im Wimmera-Gebiet auf meinen besondere Wunsch sammelt.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">8/8/92</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You will see from the enclosed sheet,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See E. Ramsay to M, 6 August 1892 (in this edition as 92-08-06a).</p>
               </note> highly esteemed Doctor, that Dr Ramsay, Director of the zoological museum of Sydney, also will subscribe to the continuation of your important <name key="Characeae">Characeae</name> monograph.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Nordstedt (1891). No further parts of the work were published.</p>
               </note> Mr Maiden in Sydney has ordered a second copy. If only we knew whether the continuation on subscription is possible, it would enable finding yet others for purchasing of the work.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Respectfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Now the excellent Schübeler has passed away too.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Schübeler died on 20 June 1892.</p>
               </note> Thus one after the other of my friends of many years have departed this life, and I suppose I, Regel, Todaro and so many others will soon follow!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You will soon receive some <name key="Characeae">Characeae</name> again, as Mr Eckert is collecting the species in the Wimmera district<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Vic.</p>
               </note> at my particular request.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Characeae">Characeae</name>
            </p>
         </div>
